# Dataset Description

## LFW (Labeled Faces in the Wild)

**Source:** http://vis-www.cs.umass.edu/lfw/  
**Full dataset size:** 13,233 images of 5,749 individuals  
**License:** Unrestricted for academic/research use  

---

## How It Is Used in This Project

This project performs **inference only — no training is done**.  
LFW is used as a source of real face image pairs for running and evaluating the face swap pipeline.  
Each run takes two LFW images:
- **Source image** — identity donor (whose face is transferred)
- **Target image** — pose/expression donor (whose head pose and expression are kept)

---

## Subset and Filtering

| Property | Value |
|---|---|
| Directory format | All images flattened into a single folder (`lfw_flat/`) — no person subfolders |
| Filtering criterion | Frontal faces only: BFM-estimated yaw angle `< 40°` |
| Pair constraint | Source and target are always different people |
| Typical pool scanned | First 200–500 randomly shuffled images per run |
| Images used per eval | 3 source-target pairs (6 images total) |

---

## Runtime Preprocessing

No offline preprocessing is applied. All steps happen at runtime:

1. Image loaded as RGB via PIL
2. Resized to `512×512` (or `192×192` in low-VRAM mode)
3. Face detected and 68 landmarks extracted via `face_alignment`
4. Head pose estimated — images with `|yaw| > 40°` are skipped
5. Tensor normalized to `[-1, 1]` before VAE encoding

---

## Train / Val / Test Split

**None.** This is a training-free inference pipeline. There is no train, validation, or test split. Quantitative evaluation is performed by running the full pipeline on 3 randomly sampled frontal pairs and computing ID-sim, SSIM, and L2 metrics.

---

## Sample Inputs

A small set of pre-selected frontal pairs is provided in `sample_inputs/` for reproducible demo and evaluation runs.

```
04_data/
└── sample_inputs/
    ├── src_1.jpg    # Identity donor — pair 1
    ├── tgt_1.jpg    # Pose donor    — pair 1
    ├── src_2.jpg
    ├── tgt_2.jpg
    ├── src_3.jpg
    └── tgt_3.jpg
```

These 6 images are the ones used in the live viva demo and for generating the results in `05_results/`.

---

## Why LFW

- Publicly available with no license restrictions for academic use
- Large enough to reliably find frontal pairs via random sampling
- Standard benchmark in face recognition literature — ID-sim scores are directly comparable to published face swap results
- Unconstrained real-world images with varied lighting, backgrounds, and poses — tests the pipeline on realistic conditions

